\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 55. C. multiflora} Sibth. & Sm.,{\i  Fl. Graec. Prodr.}{\b  2}: 138 (1813). Annual; stems 7-35 cm, branched from the base. Leaves glabrous; basal 1-5 × 0·5-1 cm, few, oblanceolate, obtuse, dentate or runcinate-pinnatifid, attenuate at base; lower cauline sessile, amplexicaul, with acute auricles; upper cauline lanceolate or linear, acute, entire. Capitula many. Involucre 8-9 × 4-6 mm bracts linear-lanceolate, acute, the outer glabrous, c. 1/3 as long as the inner, the inner with yellowish glandular hairs. Florets 7-8 mm. Ligules yellow. Achenes dark brown, of 2 kinds, or marginal absent: marginal 3·5-4 mm, more attenuate above than below, unequally ribbed; inner 3-3·5 mm, fusiform, strongly attenuate at apex, 10-ribbed, strigulose or finely spinulose near apex. 2n = 8.{\i  S.E. Greece and S. Aegean region.} Cr Gr.
