\pard\f0\fs28   Sect. ALETHOCREPIS Bischoff. Pubescent annuals or biennials; stems many, branched from near the base or middle. Lower leaves petiolate, denticulate to pinnate. Capitula many, with few to many florets. Ligules yellow, usually reddish on outer face. Receptacle usually with ciliate pits.
