\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 59. C. foliosa} Babcock,{\i  Univ. Calif. Publ. Bot.}{\b  23}: 389 (1951). Annual; glandular-pubescent throughout; stems up to 25 cm, remotely and regularly branched from the base. Basal leaves up to 9 × 2 cm, few, oblanceolate or spathulate, long-petiolate; lowest cauline oblanceolate, shortly petiolate, auriculate; upper cauline lanceolate, acuminate, dentate, sessile, amplexicaul, auriculate, the auricles about as long as the width of the lamina and narrow and acuminate. Involucre 7-8 × 4-5 mm; bracts linear-lanceolate, acute or acuminate, tomentulose and with unequal, brown glandular hairs; outer bracts c. 1/3 as long as the inner. Achenes c. 2·75 × 0·5 mm, pale brown, fusiform, 10-ribbed. •{\i  C. Ural} ({\i Utka, near Krasnoufimsk}). Rs (C).
